title: President of Kyrgyzstan - Wikipedia
snippet: Almazbek Atambayev was peacefully succeeded by Sooronbay Jeenbekov in 2017. However, Jeenbekov resigned from office due to the 2020 Kyrgyzstani protests and was succeeded by Sadyr Japarov. indicates an individual serving as an acting or provisional president of Kyrgyzstan

title: Presidents Of Kyrgyzstan Since 1991 - WorldAtlas
snippet: Kurmanbek Bakiyev was the second president of the Kyrgyzstan who served from 2005 until the government takeover in April 2010. Following the 2005 events that led to the overthrow of Akayev, Kurmanbek Bakiyev won the presidential election by 89% of the total cast votes.
